From karish Chuck Karish Subject Re Changing sprocket ratios Honda In article Clayton Brooks writes Do any Honda gurus know if I can replace the the front sprocket on my Honda with a slightly larger one I see this as being preferable to reducing the size of the rear one That's a twin cam right There's a steel guard right next to the sprocket to keep a broken chain from punching a hole in the engine cases and it's There's probably not enough room to fit a bigger I'd be inclined to take two teeth off the rear for a ratio change rather than adding one to the front for about If you raise the overall gear ratio too much you'll impair the bike's rideability because the gears will be far enough apart that there will be only one gear that provides adequate response at any given Honda don't have the widest of power Chuck Karish